## Example 3 — Simplify Logarithmic Expressions

Write

`(1/3) ln 8 - ln 3 + ln 9`

as a single logarithm.

Use the Power Property:

`= ln(8^(1/3)) - ln 3 + ln 9`

`= ln 2 - ln 3 + ln 9`

Use the Quotient Property:

`= ln(2/3) + ln 9`

Use the Product Property:

`= ln 6`

So:

`(1/3) ln 8 - ln 3 + ln 9 = ln 6`

## Think About It

