## Example 5 — Solve Natural Logarithmic Equations

Solve:

`(1/6) ln(5x) = 2`

Round to the nearest ten-thousandth.

Multiply both sides by `6`:

`ln(5x) = 12`

Rewrite exponentially:

`e^(ln(5x)) = e^12`

`5x = e^12`

`x = e^12 / 5`

`x ≈ 32,550.9583`

